{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Logs.Printers</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Logs","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Printers","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>Utility printers, that are aware of the current logging configuration.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_unstable\"><a href=\"#val-pp_unstable\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_unstable : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Wraps a pretty-printer for unstable values, that should not be output into e.g. testing environments where diffs matter. If the config option <code>hide_unstable</code> is set, will replace</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_time\"><a href=\"#val-pp_time\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_time : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>float <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a time quantity in seconds, displaying it in either seconds or milli-seconds for smaller values (&lt; 0.05s). Wrapped in <a href=\"#val-pp_unstable\"><code>pp_unstable</code></a>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_percent\"><a href=\"#val-pp_percent\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_percent : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(float * float)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>For a given value <code>(total, part)</code>, prints what percentage of <code>total</code> is represented by <code>part</code>. e.g. <code>pp_percent stdout (5.0, 1.0)</code> will print <code>20.00%</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_percenti\"><a href=\"#val-pp_percenti\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_percenti : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(int * int)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Same as <a href=\"#val-pp_percent\"><code>pp_percent</code></a>, but for integer values (implicitly converts to float).</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_plural\"><a href=\"#val-pp_plural\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_plural : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">sing</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">plur</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span>int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Prints <code>1 sing</code> if <code>n = 1</code>, <code>n plur</code> otherwise.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_clr\"><a href=\"#val-pp_clr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_clr : <span><a href=\"../Color/index.html#type-t\">Color.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string with a given color</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_style\"><a href=\"#val-pp_style\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_style : <span><a href=\"../Color/index.html#type-style\">Color.style</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string with a given style</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_clr2\"><a href=\"#val-pp_clr2\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_clr2 : \u000A  <span><a href=\"../Color/index.html#type-t\">Color.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><a href=\"../Color/index.html#type-style\">Color.style</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string with a given color and style</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_ok\"><a href=\"#val-pp_ok\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_ok : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string as an &quot;ok&quot;-colored message</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_err\"><a href=\"#val-pp_err\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_err : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string as an &quot;error&quot;-colored message</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_fatal\"><a href=\"#val-pp_fatal\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_fatal : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string as a &quot;fatal&quot;-colored message</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_warn\"><a href=\"#val-pp_warn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_warn : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Pretty-prints a string as a &quot;warning&quot;-colored message</p></div></div>"}